<div>
  <p>
    This demo uses lossy compression (MozJPEG) to reduce the image sizes. Each
    image was compressed manually and different settings were used on each one.
    For the 1920w image I used a quality of 50 and reduced the color
    palette slightly. For the 1280w and 640w image I kept the full 256 colors and used a
    quality of 80.
  </p>
  <div class="gallery">
    <div class="large">
      <img
        id="image"
        alt="Photograph of a group of pedestrians crossing the street."
        width="640"
        height="426"
        src="/images/image-640-lossy.jpg?v=4"
        srcset="/images/image-640-lossy.jpg?v=4 640w, /images/image-1280-lossy.jpg?v=4 1280w, /images/image-1920-lossy.jpg?v=4 1920w"
        sizes="(min-width: 540px) 640px, calc(100vw - 2rem)"
